<TITLE> Mamun, Loby remanded </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 6 (bdnews24.com) -- A Dhaka court Wednesday sent controversial businessman Giasuddin Al Mamun and BNP leader Ali Asghar Loby into remand. Interrogators will question Mamun, known as business partner of Tarique Rahman, for five days while Loby will be quizzed for three days. Metropolitan magistrate MA Salam issued the order after the police sought a seven-day remand for each. Gulshan sub-inspector Rawshan Ali sought the remand for Loby in a case of land grab and burglary. According to case details, Loby and his associates allegedly grabbed a house on August 14, 2003. They threatened the homeowner with firearms and took away Tk 10,000. On March 11, Md Jakaria Khan Julu filed the case against Loby with Gulshan Police Station. Meanwhile, another Gulshan sub-inspector, Moinul Islam, appealed for Mamun's remand on charge of extorting Tk 840.62 crore. On May 31, Japan-Bangladesh Company chairman Selim Pradhan filed the case against Mamun with Gulshan Police Station. bdnews24
